    {
      "title": "Protocol 3: The BC Protocol, BCPE\nEach process Pi executes the following (track 1):\n1S. Consistently exchange Input with all processes using BCE Propose(Input)\n2E. If BCE Decide(), the decision value from the consistent exchange, 6= ⊥, then:\n—- Set MyStatus ← True\n3S. Byzantine Broadcast MyStatus to all processes using BB Broadcasti(MyStatus)\nLE. Set Status[j] ← BB Deliverj(), the bit Byzantine broadcasted by Pj\nEach process Pi executes the following (track 2):\n1S. Set InSymbols ← ENC(Input, n, n − 2f), the codeword describing Input\nConsistently broadcast InSymbols[i] to all processes using\nBCB Broadcasti(InSymbols[i])\n—- ∗ Note that ENC() is also performed as a part of BCE in track 1. Thus, it does not\n—- ∗ need to be repeated here. Moreover, InSymbols[i] is sent to all other processes in round\n—- ∗ 1 of BCE in track 1. Thus, it does not need to be sent again in round 1 of BCB.\n3E. Set Symbols[j] ← BCB Deliverj(), the symbol consistently broadcasted by Pj\n4S. If MyStatus = True, then:\n—- Send SYN(InSymbols, Symbols) to all other processes\n4E. Set Syndromes[j] ← the syndrome sent by Pj (if any)\nEach process Pi executes the following (after tracks 1 and 2):\nLE. If < n − f bits in Status are True, then:\n—- Decide on default value D\nElse if MyStatus = T rue, then:\n—- Decide on Input\nElse:",
